Person 2 – How to Give Feedback Professionally
Give feedback at the right time.
Focus on behavior, not the person.
Be specific instead of general.
Balance positive and constructive feedback.
Offer suggestions for improvement.
Example:
Instead of saying "Your report is bad," say "The report is well-structured, but adding more data analysis will make it stronger."

Formula for Good Feedback
SBI Model
Situation – When?
Behavior – What happened?
Impact – What was the result?
Example:
"During today's meeting, your clear explanation helped the team understand the project faster."
